request_text: Provisions of all instances where TECHNICAL Violations for Complaint I00300448 were stated to have happened or have not to have happened. This is not a duplicative request as from email request, the FOIA Request had the ‘technical’ aspect removed, and when it was finally allegedly rendered, it did not provide any information related to TECHNICAL violations. A technical violation is anything that would not be in compliance with Section 503 or VEVRAA  or other statute and thus in violation of it. Examples of places where technical violations may have occurred would be in emails requesting a Compliance Check upon the Contractor, the Investigative Report, or in Phone Calls & Transcripts by the Investigator.
